# Cursor Rules for Project

## 1. Technology Stack
- Next.js 13+ with App Router
- TypeScript for type safety
- Supabase for backend
- TailwindCSS for styling
- Vercel for deployment

## 2. Coding Standards & Style
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Prefer functional components
- Use ES6+ features
- Maintain consistent error handling
- Follow React best practices
- Use proper TypeScript types/interfaces

## 3. Naming Conventions
- PascalCase for components
- camelCase for functions and variables
- Use descriptive, meaningful names
- Prefix interfaces with 'I' (optional)
- Prefix type aliases with 'T' (optional)
- Use consistent naming across similar items

## 4. Syntax and Formatting
- 2 space indentation
- Semicolons required
- Single quotes for strings
- Trailing commas in multiline
- Max line length: 100 characters
- Consistent component structure
- Clear component/function separation

## 5. UI and Styling
- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Maintain responsive design
- Follow accessibility standards
- Consistent color schemes
- Maintain dark mode support
- Use CSS modules when needed

## 6. Key Conventions
- Keep components small and focused
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use proper state management
- Maintain clean props interface
- Document complex logic
- Follow DRY principles
- Implement proper loading states
- Handle edge cases appropriately
